31/01/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The OSCE Mission in Macedonia launches a project Tuesday (31 January) to train border police. 
Under the initiative, a three-week training course is to be held for officers from each of the country's 30 border police stations, aimed at improving first-aid skills. 
More courses are to be organised in the next three months.
In other news, Macedonian Army Chief General Miroslav Stojanovski issued a statement Monday, confirming that a war crimes investigation against him has been dropped. 
Croatian prosecutors determined that he was not involved in 1991 crimes committed against Croatian civilians in Vukovar. 
(OSCE Web site, Telma TV, A1 TV - 30/01/06)
